FODMAP Helper Website Specification

ROLE You are an award-winning UI/UX designer and senior front-end
developer.

Design and build a single-page responsive website called FODMAP Helper.

Inspiration: - Bloom
(https://bloom-fluid-demo.squarespace.com/?nochrome=true) - Apple -
Headspace - Oura - Calm

Do not copy Bloom exactly; use it as inspiration for spacing,
typography, editorial layout, and premium wellness aesthetic.

TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS - HTML5 - CSS3 - Vanilla JavaScript - No
frameworks (Bootstrap, Tailwind, React, jQuery, etc.)

Deliver: - index.html - style.css - script.js

Responsive: - Desktop - Tablet - Mobile

Typography: - Google Font: Raleway - Large elegant headings -
Comfortable whitespace

Palette: Background: #FAF8F4 Primary: #4A7C59 Secondary: #7AAB8A Accent:
#C8624A Text: #2D3B35

SECTIONS 1. Fullscreen Hero with transparent navigation, logo, CTA,
parallax background. 2. About Low FODMAP explaining IBS and the three
phases: - Elimination - Reintroduction - Personalisation 3. Foods You
Can Eat: Vegetables, Fruit, Proteins, Grains, Dairy Alternatives, Nuts &
Seeds, Herbs, Oils. Include 20–30 foods per category. 4. Foods To Avoid
grouped by: - Fructans - GOS - Lactose - Excess Fructose - Polyols 5.
Food comparison cards (safe vs avoid). 6. Seven-day meal inspiration. 7.
Recipe section with at least 24 recipes including ingredients,
instructions, prep time, nutrition, Low FODMAP notes, and difficulty. 8.
Around 30 practical Low FODMAP tips. 9. FAQ accordion with about 20
questions. 10. Footer with disclaimer, social icons, and helpful links.

DESIGN - Premium wellness aesthetic - Large food photography - Rounded
cards - Organic shapes - Glassmorphism navigation - Soft gradients -
Smooth shadows

ANIMATIONS - CSS parallax - Fade-in - Slide-up - Hover animations -
Smooth scrolling - Floating elements - Intersection Observer reveals -
Navigation shrink on scroll

IMAGES Use royalty-free placeholder images from Unsplash or Pexels
featuring healthy meals, vegetables, fruit, nature, kitchens, and
wellness.

ACCESSIBILITY - Semantic HTML - ARIA labels - Keyboard navigation - WCAG
AA contrast

PERFORMANCE - Lazy-load images - Optimised CSS and JavaScript

SEO - Meta description - Open Graph tags - Proper heading hierarchy -
Alt text

CODE QUALITY - Well commented - CSS variables - CSS Grid + Flexbox -
Reusable components - Avoid duplicated code

GOAL The finished website should look like a professionally designed
commercial wellness website that exceeds the quality of the Bloom
inspiration while remaining clean, elegant, and editorial.
